  "name": "Verdurous Ooze",
  "pfs": {
    "availability": "Standard",
    "subtype": "pfs",
    "type": "stat_block_section"
  },
  "schema_version": 1.4,
  "sections": [
    {
      "name": "Verdurous Ooze",
      "sections": [
        {
          "image": {
            "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png",
            "name": "Additional Lore",
            "type": "image"
          },
          "name": "Verdurous Congregation",
          "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
          "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 242",
                "aonid": 276,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 242",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Monster Core 2",
              "page": 242,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "subtype": "sidebar",
          "text": "When verdurous oozes gather in sufficient number, they can merge together into conjoined forms. These enlarged blobs develop red and white connecting vessels that pulse hideously as thick, green fluid moves within them. While conjoined, the oozes move as one creature. Their usual enliven foliage and Sleep Gas auras double in size, and they become even more aggressive, feeding voraciously on any metal or flesh they can find.",
          "type": "section"
        }
      ],
      "sources": [
        {
          "link": {
            "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 242",
            "aonid": 276,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 242",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "Monster Core 2",
          "page": 242,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "Verdurous oozes are found in temperate forests, warm jungles, or other places where plant life grows in abundance. Unlike many types of oozes, verdurous oozes are not particularly good climbers and have been known to get trapped in natural or artificial chasms. Warlords and wizards sometimes make use of that fact and keep verdurous oozes as guardians in pits around the walls of their fortresses or towers.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
  "sources": [
    {
      "link": {
        "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 242",
        "aonid": 276,
        "game-obj": "Sources",
        "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 242",
        "type": "link"
      },
      "name": "Monster Core 2",
      "page": 242,
      "type": "source"
    }
  ],
  "stat_block": {
    "creature_type": {
      "creature_types": [
        "Mindless",
        "Ooze"
      ],
      "family": {
        "alternate_link": {
